The paper deals with the problem of fingerprint liveness detection, which is a subfield of computer vision (cs.CV) and computer security (cs.CR). The use of Convolutional Networks and Local Binary Patterns for feature extraction and Support Vector Machines for classification suggests that the paper may also fall under the subcategories of machine learning (cs.LG) and multimedia (cs.MM). Finally, the preprocessing techniques used in the paper, such as frequency filtering and contrast equalization, suggest that the paper may also be relevant to the subfield of information retrieval (cs.IR).
